<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Marquesas Islands: Ua Huka: Summit of ridge near Hitikau, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Malvaceae" genus="Hibiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tiliaceus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Hibiscus tiliaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest, 820 m, 28 June 1997, S. Perlman, K. Wood, &amp; J.-Y. Meyer 15844 (holotype: PTBG-026355!; isotype: US!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Shrubs 1-2 m tall; stems apparently few. Leaves opposite, borne on upper 2-5 nodes, broadly elliptic, 18-26 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
7-10 cm, lower surface densely ferruginous appressed pubescent, upper surface glabrate, irregularly dentate, the teeth variable in size, petiole 5-6.5 cm, ferruginous appressed to spreading pubescent. Flowers in cymes arising in the upper leaf axils, apparently 1-3 flowered, peduncle 0-2 mm, ca. 1-2 mm in diameter, pedicels up to 6 mm; calyx cylindrical-ellipsoid, white, plicate; corolla much longer than calyx; style up to 10 mm, flower parts otherwise unknown. Partly mature berries up to 14 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Marquesas Islands, rare, endemic to Hitikau summit area, Ua Huka, from 820-870 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Lorence" authorityYear="2013" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="uahukaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Cyrtandra uahukaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="B. C. Stone" authorityYear="1968" baseAuthorityName="Hombr. &amp; Jacquinot ex Decne." class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Freycinetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Pandanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="impavida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Freycinetia impavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Malvaceae" genus="Hibiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tiliaceus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Hibiscus tiliaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shrubland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">The specific epithet refers to the island of Ua Huka where the only known populations occur.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
IUCN Red List Category: Critically Endangered CR B2a + 2b (i, ii, iii). B2: total area of occupancy less than 10 km2 (ca. 5 km2). B2a, a single population known; b (i-iii), habitat continuing decline inferred. The suitable habitat for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Lorence" authorityYear="2013" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="uahukaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Cyrtandra uahukaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Ua Huka (ca. 83 km2) is indicated as an endangered environment, threatened feral animals, and invasive plants, reducing the extent of the forest (
<bibRefCitation author="Florence, J" journalOrPublisher="Allertonia" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="226 - 237" refId="B8" refString="Florence, J, Lorence, DH, 1997. Introduction to the flora and vegetation of the Marquesas Islands. Allertonia 7: 226 - 237" title="Introduction to the flora and vegetation of the Marquesas Islands." volume="7" year="1997">Florence and Lorence 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mueller-Dombois, D" journalOrPublisher="Springer, New York" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="444 - 460" refId="B14" refString="Mueller-Dombois, D, Fosberg, FR, 1998. Marquesas. Vegetation of the Tropical Pacific Islands. Springer, New York: 444 - 460" title="Marquesas. Vegetation of the Tropical Pacific Islands." year="1998">Mueller-Dombois and Fosberg 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer, J-Y" editor="Gillespie, RG" journalOrPublisher="University of California Press, Berkeley" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="332 - 338" refId="B13" refString="Meyer, J-Y, Salvat, B, 2009. French Polynesia, Biology. In: Gillespie, RG, Clague, DA, Eds., Encyclopedia of Islands. University of California Press, Berkeley: 332 - 338" title="French Polynesia, Biology." volumeTitle="Encyclopedia of Islands." year="2009">Meyer and Salvat 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
